.TH "dce_v10_0_line_buffer_adjust" 9 "dce_v10_0_line_buffer_adjust" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dce_v10_0_line_buffer_adjust \- Set up the line buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" dce_v10_0_line_buffer_adjust
.BI "(struct amdgpu_device *adev "  ","
.BI "struct amdgpu_crtc *amdgpu_crtc "  ","
.BI "struct drm_display_mode *mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adev" 12
amdgpu_device pointer
.IP "amdgpu_crtc" 12
the selected display controller
.IP "mode" 12
the current display mode on the selected display
controller
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Setup up the line buffer allocation for
the selected display controller (CIK).
Returns the line buffer size in pixels.
